name: pycocotools

pre_pr_migrator_status.pypy37: not solvable: master: ['linux_aarch64_python3.7.____73_pypy: Encountered problems while solving.\nProblem: nothing provides openssl >=1.0.2p,<1.0.3a needed by python-3.6.7-hd21baee_1002\n']

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pycocotools" %}
{% set version = "2.0.6" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 7fe089b05cc18e806dcf3bd764708d86dab922a100f3734eb77fb77a70a1d18c

build:
  number: 1
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed -vvv

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cython                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - numpy                                  # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - setuptools
    - cython
    - matplotlib-base
    - numpy
  run:
    - python
    - cython
    - matplotlib-base
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}

test:
  imports:
    - pycocotools
    - pycocotools.mask

about:
  home: https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: license.txt
  summary: Library to work with COCO dataset.
  doc_url: http://cocodataset.org
  dev_url: https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - erykoff
